You are about to install Thunderbird-portable.

It can be installed on harddrive (ssd) or any removeable drive,
it will survive changes of drive name (usb).

To reinstall or change drive locations just type tbinst in
a terminal or go to /usr/local/bin and click on tbinst

The first click on Menu->Internet->Thunderbird-portable will ask
you to install and then it will start Thunderbird.  From then on 
clicking Menu->Internet->Thunderbird-portable
will start Thunderbird.

After your first run of Thunderbird you will be asked if you
want to make it your default email client:
tbportable_launch "$@"
will be entered in /usr/local/bin/defautemail